abstract: Ian Urbina travel article recounts trip to one of crown jewels of Pacific archipelago nation of Palau, Jellyfish Lake; 12-acre saltwater lake off Rock Islands, Unesco World Heritage site, offers visitors chance to slip into fluorescent-green waters bobbing with millions of jellyfish; lake is considered one of seven aquatic wonders of world.
